AB  - Efficiency analysis is concerned with isolating the efficient subset of investments (portfolios) for all investors belonging to a specified group. In order to construct a meaningful efficiency criterion, i.e., one which holds for more than one investor, care must be exercised to ensure that the investors' efficient set is independent of their wealth.
